{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/science/functional-analysis-and-graph-theory","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<ol>\n<li>The theory of continuous graphs also known as <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graphon\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\"><em>graphons</em></a> heavily relies on functional analysis of the Lebesgue space <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">L_1</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">L</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3011em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> as one has to deal with certain limits of discrete objects with respect to the norm of <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">L_1</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mat